chain
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a) the overhead chain on which carcasses move for processing in a freezing works; b) the specialist workers who work at various points along such a chain; drag the chain, to be slow (usual constr. the); the work-line on which each of a specialised group of men works consecutively from killing to completing the dressing of carcases; the killing-chain (also go down the chain, give a cut up the chain, beef chain, mutton chain etc).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
